166 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe (int32_t argc, char* argv[], int32_t expectedArgc, int8_t* subFrameNum)
167 {
168  int8_t subframe;
169 
170  /* Sanity Check: Minimum argument check */
171  if (argc != expectedArgc)
172  {
173  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid usage of the CLI command\n");
174  return -1;
175  }
176 
177  /*Subframe info is always in position 1*/
178  subframe = (int8_t) atoi(argv[1]);
179 
180  if(subframe >= (int8_t)RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES)
181  {
182  CLI_write ("Error: Subframe number is invalid\n");
183  return -1;
184  }
185 
186  *subFrameNum = (int8_t)subframe;
187 
188  return 0;
189 }

191 static void MmwDemo_mssCfgUpdate(void *srcPtr, uint32_t offset, uint32_t size, int8_t subFrameNum)
192 {
193  /* if subFrameNum undefined, broadcast to all sub-frames */
194  if(subFrameNum == MMWDEMO_SUBFRAME_NUM_FRAME_LEVEL_CONFIG)
195  {
196  uint8_t indx;
197  for(indx = 0; indx < RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES; indx++)
198  {
199  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.cliCfg[indx] + offset), srcPtr, size);
200  }
201 
202  }
203  else
204  {
205  /* Apply configuration to specific subframe (or to position zero for the legacy case
206  where there is no advanced frame config) */
207  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwMssMCB.cliCfg[subFrameNum] + offset), srcPtr, size);
208  }
209 }

450 uint32_t log2Approx(uint32_t x)
451 {
452  uint32_t idx, detectFlag = 0;
453 
454  if ( x < 2)
455  {
456  return (0);
457  }
458 
459  idx = 32U;
460  while((detectFlag==0U) || (idx==0U))
461  {
462  if(x & 0x80000000U)
463  {
464  detectFlag = 1;
465  }
466  x <<= 1U;
467  idx--;
468  }
469 
470  if(x != 0)
471  {
472  idx = idx + 1;
473  }
474 
475  return(idx);
476 }

493 static int32_t MmwDemo_CLICalibDcRangeSig (int32_t argc, char* argv[])
494 {
495  MmwDemo_CalibDcRangeSigCfg cfg;
496  MmwDemo_message message;
497  uint32_t log2NumAvgChirps;
498  int8_t subFrameNum;
499 
500  if(MmwDemo_CLIGetSubframe(argc, argv, 6, &subFrameNum) < 0)
501  {
502  return -1;
503  }
504 
505  /* Initialize configuration for DC range signature calibration */
506  memset ((void *)&cfg, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_CalibDcRangeSigCfg));
507 
508  /* Populate configuration: */
509  cfg.enabled = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[2]);
510  cfg.negativeBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[3]);
511  cfg.positiveBinIdx = (int16_t) atoi (argv[4]);
512  cfg.numAvgChirps = (uint16_t) atoi (argv[5]);
513 
514  if (cfg.negativeBinIdx > 0)
515  {
516  CLI_write ("Error: Invalid negative bin index\n");
517  return -1;
518  }
519  if ((cfg.positiveBinIdx - cfg.negativeBinIdx + 1) > DC_RANGE_SIGNATURE_COMP_MAX_BIN_SIZE)
520  {
521  CLI_write ("Error: Number of bins exceeds the limit\n");
522  return -1;
523  }
524  log2NumAvgChirps = (uint32_t) log2Approx (cfg.numAvgChirps);
525  if (cfg.numAvgChirps != (1 << log2NumAvgChirps))
526  {
527  CLI_write ("Error: Number of averaged chirps is not power of two\n");
528  return -1;
529  }
530 
531  /* Save Configuration to use later */
532  MmwDemo_mssCfgUpdate((void *)&cfg, offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, calibDcRangeSigCfg),
533  sizeof(MmwDemo_CalibDcRangeSigCfg), subFrameNum);
534 
535  /* Send configuration to DSS */
536  memset((void *)&message, 0, sizeof(MmwDemo_message));
537 
538  message.type = MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_CALIB_DC_RANGE_SIG;
539  message.subFrameNum = subFrameNum;
540  memcpy((void *)&message.body.calibDcRangeSigCfg, (void *)&cfg, sizeof(MmwDemo_CalibDcRangeSigCfg));
541 
542  if (MmwDemo_mboxWrite(&message) == 0)
543  return 0;
544  else
545  return -1;
546 }
